body:
@Osmose Ok -- everything from round 2 of review has been fixed or at least addressed in some way. 

The tests are hard. You're right that they are too tightly coupled to the HTML. If we do a [shallow render](https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/test-utils.html#shallow-rendering) like in the recipeForm test, that's really all we can test - the HTML. I ran into a lot of problems trying to do a full render in order to test the methods on the components (setting up a store, having to import all dependencies for child components, etc), so testing the HTML at least provided _some_ kind of validation that interactions were working as expected.

That said, there's now something wrong with importing the component files for testing purposes anyway. So I will work on those. But feel free to review the other changes in the meantime.

